-- Goldin to Issue Up to HK$5.08 Billion of Convertible Bonds to Shareholders
-- B y   J o s h u a   F e l l m a n
-- 2010-10-15T15:16:14Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-15/goldin-to-issue-up-to-hk-5-08-billion-of-convertible-bonds-to-shareholders.html
Goldin Properties Holdings Ltd . said
it will raise as much as HK$5.08 billion through on offer of
convertible bonds to shareholders to strengthen its financial
position.  The company will over two units of convertible bonds at
HK$6 apiece for every three shares held, Goldin said in a Hong
Kong stock exchange filing today. Net cash proceeds, after
expenses and repayment of a $300 million shareholders loan, will
be as much as HK$2.68 billion, the company said.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Joshua Fellman at 
 jfellman@bloomberg.net  